meta {
  name: GET charging modes (v2.10.0 Group B)
  type: http
  seq: 45
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/charging/modes
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 Group B - Backend-allowed charging modes list.

  Returns the list of charging mode enum strings the backend
  currently allows for the vehicle. Surfaced as an attribute on
  the existing ``charging_preferred_mode`` sensor under
  ``available_modes`` instead of a dedicated entity, so the surface
  stays clean while still being template-addressable.

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Charging Modes sequence), independently parsed in
  ``seat_cupra.get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape (observed):
    {
      "availableChargeModes": [
        "manual",
        "preferredChargingTimes",
        "automaticUnlocked"
      ]
    }

  Variants tried defensively: top-level list, nested under
  ``modes``, nested under ``chargeModes``, nested under
  ``data.modes``. The parser accepts entries as plain strings or
  as dicts with a ``name`` / ``id`` / ``mode`` field.

  Companion PUT lives in the ``update_charging_settings`` HA service
  which targets POST
  ``/v1/vehicles/{vin}/charging/actions/update-settings`` (Bruno seq
  46 in a future expansion).

  Soft-fails to ``{}`` on 401 / 403 / 404.
}
